      "question": "A technician is repairing a circuit board where the flow of current is controlled by two resistors, $R_1$ and $R_2$. The relationship between the resistances (in ohms) is given by the following system of equations involving the reciprocals of the resistances, where $x = \\frac{1}{R_1}$ and $y = \\frac{1}{R_2}$:\n(1) $\\frac{2}{R_1} + \\frac{3}{R_2} = 1.3$\n(2) $\\frac{5}{R_1} - \\frac{4}{R_2} = -0.1$\nBased on this, answer the following sub-questions.",
